        <gcds-heading tag="h2" id="responsive" margin-bottom="300">Responsive Utilities</gcds-heading>
            <gcds-text margin-bottom="300">
                Responsive utilities allow you to show/hide elements at different screen sizes:
            </gcds-text>
            
            <div class="table-responsive fdcp-mb-400">
                <table class="table table-striped">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Class</th>
                            <th>Breakpoint</th>
                            <th>Description</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr><td><code>.fdcp-d-sm-none</code></td><td>≥576px</td><td>Hide on small screens and up</td></tr>
                        <tr><td><code>.fdcp-d-md-flex</code></td><td>≥768px</td><td>Show as flex on medium screens and up</td></tr>
                        <tr><td><code>.fdcp-d-lg-block</code></td><td>≥992px</td><td>Show as block on large screens and up</td></tr>
                        <tr><td><code>.fdcp-d-xl-none</code></td><td>≥1200px</td><td>Hide on extra large screens and up</td></tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>

            <div class="fdcp-bg-gray-50 fdcp-p-300">
                <gcds-heading tag="h4" margin-bottom="200">Example Usage:</gcds-heading>
                <pre class="fdcp-mb-0"><code>&lt;!-- Hide on mobile, show on desktop --&gt;
&lt;div class="fdcp-d-none fdcp-d-md-block"&gt;
  This content is hidden on mobile but visible on tablets and larger
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- Show on mobile, hide on desktop --&gt;
&lt;div class="fdcp-d-block fdcp-d-md-none"&gt;
  This content is visible on mobile but hidden on tablets and larger
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
        </div>

